WEBVTT

00:04.130 --> 00:05.763
He's on the move.

00:05.765 --> 00:08.750
Heading south on Broadway
towards 46th Street.

00:11.087 --> 00:12.220
Cuckoo!

00:12.222 --> 00:13.521
You're screwed!

00:14.524 --> 00:15.857
(grunts)

00:15.859 --> 00:17.308
All right, all right,
all right.

00:17.310 --> 00:19.477
(squawks)
Calm down.

00:19.479 --> 00:20.862
I'm Lieutenant McCarthy, sir.
How are you doing today?

00:20.864 --> 00:23.231
And I'm crazy! Sir!

00:23.233 --> 00:24.449
Why don't you just step down,

00:24.451 --> 00:25.950
and we can talk, okay?

00:25.952 --> 00:27.652
No, no, no. Screw you!

00:27.654 --> 00:29.404
And you! And you!

00:29.406 --> 00:30.955
All of you!

00:30.957 --> 00:33.207
What are you looking at, huh?

00:33.209 --> 00:34.575
(man spits, crowd gasps)

00:34.577 --> 00:35.874
Food for the needy!
Hey, hey! Come on now.

00:35.875 --> 00:37.855
Not for the greedy!

00:37.856 --> 00:38.547
Move the perimeter back
50 feet immediately.

00:38.548 --> 00:42.333
Food for the needy!
Not for the greedy!

00:42.335 --> 00:44.919
Screw you! Come on.
See if you can lay a hand on him, okay?

00:44.921 --> 00:46.421
Screw you all!
Sir, you need

00:46.423 --> 00:48.423
to step down immediately, okay?

00:48.425 --> 00:50.925
(man making martial arts sounds)

00:50.927 --> 00:53.327
Yah! Hey!
Get away from me.

00:53.329 --> 00:54.812
Sir, get down.
Don't you touch me.

00:54.814 --> 00:57.465
I'll kick your ass.
You want some money?

00:57.467 --> 01:00.501
Ow! Mommy!
Hey, watch the girl.

01:00.503 --> 01:02.854
Yah! Hah!
Use the stun gun.

01:02.856 --> 01:06.274
Price check! Price check!
Price check!

01:06.276 --> 01:07.658
Price check!

01:07.660 --> 01:09.327
(stun gun clicking)
Price check!

01:09.329 --> 01:11.362
(tires screeching,
people screaming)

01:13.700 --> 01:15.583
Oh, God.

01:17.587 --> 01:19.087
Do you know
what Monday is?

01:19.089 --> 01:20.371
No.

01:20.373 --> 01:22.256
The anniversary...

01:22.258 --> 01:23.591
Whose?

01:23.593 --> 01:25.293
Ours.

01:26.179 --> 01:28.096
What?
As partners.

01:28.098 --> 01:31.048
It's been exactly a year,
which means--

01:31.050 --> 01:34.352
Monday, my probationary period
is officially over.

01:35.972 --> 01:37.021
Congratulations.

01:37.023 --> 01:38.973
Thank you.

01:38.975 --> 01:40.558
Where you gonna take me?

01:42.228 --> 01:45.113
Oh, first of all, you <i> know</i>
you lucked out with me.

01:45.115 --> 01:46.697
Second of all, we need
to celebrate the fact

01:46.699 --> 01:48.149
that I'm now
officially your equal.

01:48.151 --> 01:49.567
Let's not go too far.

01:49.569 --> 01:51.652
I've still got a lot more hours
on the job.

01:51.654 --> 01:53.821
Mm-hmm.
DISPATCHER: 12-David, be advised.

01:53.823 --> 01:56.045
We're receiving a 52,
domestic disturbance,

01:56.070 --> 01:56.826
Oh, man.

01:56.826 --> 01:58.242
at 190 West End Avenue.

01:58.244 --> 02:01.245
Why is it every time
I'm eating... we get a job?

02:01.247 --> 02:03.865
Maybe 'cause
you're always eating.

02:04.751 --> 02:06.284
Oh...

02:07.620 --> 02:09.287
Happy dust,

02:09.288 --> 02:11.289
pebbles, pills,

02:11.291 --> 02:12.457
hash,

02:12.459 --> 02:14.175
meth.

02:14.177 --> 02:15.460
You seeing this?

02:15.462 --> 02:17.795
There's got to be $30 million
worth of drugs here.

02:17.797 --> 02:19.797
It's got to be
a hundred degrees out, Reagan.

02:19.799 --> 02:23.017
Will you come on, lighten up.

02:23.019 --> 02:24.051
It's overtime.

02:24.053 --> 02:25.720
Besides, I brought you
an iced coffee.

02:25.722 --> 02:27.121
Rick Siblano, DEA.

02:27.123 --> 02:29.474
Susan Martinez,
one of our lab techs.

02:29.476 --> 02:31.943
Just for the record,
this guy never buys <i> me</i> a coffee.

02:31.945 --> 02:33.895
She'll be driving the truck.

02:33.897 --> 02:36.564
Just for the record, this guy
never lets anyone else drive.

02:36.566 --> 02:37.982
Come on. She's just mad

02:37.984 --> 02:39.901
'cause I talked her into
the detail, that's all.

02:39.903 --> 02:41.819
So, what's
the story here?

02:41.821 --> 02:44.205
We're going to, uh, escort
$30 million in confiscated drugs

02:44.207 --> 02:45.706
with just a truck
and two unmarked cars?

02:45.708 --> 02:46.908
Is that the plan?

02:46.910 --> 02:48.543
Yeah, it keeps it
under the radar.

02:48.545 --> 02:52.046
It's all overtime for me--
I got to get my kid new braces.

02:53.833 --> 02:55.550
All right, let's hit the road.

02:55.552 --> 02:57.685
We'll be the follow car.

02:58.671 --> 03:00.004
Oh, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa.

03:00.006 --> 03:03.341
Whoa, whoa.
You've got shotgun.

03:07.981 --> 03:09.430
(siren wailing)

03:09.432 --> 03:11.432
MAN: You think I'm stupid, huh?
(woman gasps)

03:11.434 --> 03:13.184
Why is he calling you?
Stop it.

03:13.186 --> 03:14.535
Police!
You think I'm dumb? Huh?

03:14.537 --> 03:15.703
Hey!
You think I'm stupid?

03:15.705 --> 03:18.022
You think I'm stupid?
Stop! Hey!

03:18.024 --> 03:19.023
Sir, step back.
He's crazy!

03:19.025 --> 03:20.408
Sir, I said step back.
All right.

03:20.410 --> 03:22.577
You want to tell me what's going on?
She's a lying bitch!

03:22.579 --> 03:23.995
Okay, who is she?
Is she your girlfriend?

03:23.997 --> 03:25.162
What are you saying?
And then...

03:25.164 --> 03:27.331
Know what? Don't worry
about her. Calm down.

03:27.333 --> 03:29.500
Hey. Settle down now.
WOMAN: I didn't do anything.

03:29.502 --> 03:31.285
Get the hell
away from me.

03:31.287 --> 03:32.787
(grunts)

03:32.789 --> 03:36.290
Hey, hey, hey, back up, back up.
Stop. Stop!

03:36.292 --> 03:38.593
Jamie. Jamie.
What are you doing?

03:38.595 --> 03:40.378
You're hurting him.

03:40.380 --> 03:42.263
(screams) Stop!
Hey, hey, hey.

03:42.265 --> 03:43.714
Calm down.

03:43.716 --> 03:45.182
Let go of me.
Calm down, hey.

03:45.184 --> 03:47.885
Where's the tough guy now, huh?

03:48.972 --> 03:50.137
Enough!

03:51.274 --> 03:53.808
RENZULLI:
You-- step away.

03:53.810 --> 03:55.560
And you--

03:55.562 --> 03:57.511
you're under arrest, genius.

03:59.000 --> 04:05.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

04:16.165 --> 04:18.632
It was a judgment call.

04:18.635 --> 04:20.834
It was a <i> bad</i>
judgment call.

04:20.837 --> 04:22.837
He caused the death
of an innocent civilian.

04:22.839 --> 04:24.972
Innocent? The guy was
a threat to pedestrians

04:24.974 --> 04:26.641
and to my officers.

04:26.643 --> 04:27.758
Frank, this is neglect.

04:27.760 --> 04:30.227
Criminal neglect,
reckless endangerment.

04:30.229 --> 04:33.564
You're fitting him for a noose.

04:33.566 --> 04:36.651
McCarthy's facing a charge of
criminally negligent homicide.

04:36.653 --> 04:38.319
What happened
to an investigation?

04:38.321 --> 04:41.489
The DA will decide to indict
based on their findings.

04:41.491 --> 04:42.773
And they're requesting

04:42.775 --> 04:45.493
that you not speak with
McCarthy, pending that decision.

04:47.363 --> 04:50.748
You're telling me not
to speak to my own men?

04:52.619 --> 04:54.752
Frank, that's exactly
what I'm telling you.

04:56.289 --> 04:58.122
How do you want
to handle the press?

04:58.124 --> 05:00.091
My office will schedule
a press conference.

05:00.093 --> 05:02.243
Am I allowed to speak at that?

05:02.245 --> 05:04.595
Or should I just smile and nod?

05:04.597 --> 05:07.598
Frank, if that were
only possible.

05:13.139 --> 05:14.855
When you and Linda go out
in the car together,

05:14.857 --> 05:15.973
do you always drive?

05:15.975 --> 05:18.225
Most of the time.

05:18.227 --> 05:19.727
What's “most of the time”?

05:19.729 --> 05:21.529
50 percent? 90 percent?

05:21.531 --> 05:23.114
I mean, I'm just curious.

05:23.116 --> 05:26.200
I drive her 99.9
percent of the time.

05:26.202 --> 05:28.452
She's a lousy driver. Why?

05:28.454 --> 05:31.072
What's going on with you, huh?

05:35.578 --> 05:37.328
(groans)

05:39.749 --> 05:41.832
(grunts)

05:45.138 --> 05:46.470
You okay?

05:46.472 --> 05:49.256
I don't know, I don't know.
You all right?

05:49.258 --> 05:51.926
5-4 detectives to Central.
(groans)

05:51.928 --> 05:53.978
(gunshots)
We got shots fired!

05:53.980 --> 05:55.896
It's an ambush.
Stay down. Stay down.

05:55.898 --> 05:57.264
Get your piece out.

05:57.266 --> 06:00.067
(gunfire continues)
Stay down!

06:20.373 --> 06:22.373
(gunfire continues)

06:22.375 --> 06:24.375
(men shouting)

06:24.377 --> 06:26.544
(woman whimpers)

06:27.380 --> 06:29.547
(gunfire continues)

06:31.434 --> 06:33.601
(woman screams)

06:37.473 --> 06:38.939
(screams)
Let's go, man!

06:39.442 --> 06:42.476
(screaming)

06:42.478 --> 06:44.945
We've got to go.
Let's go, hurry up. Let's go.

06:49.485 --> 06:51.535
(grunts)

07:03.916 --> 07:06.083
(grunts)

07:08.471 --> 07:09.887
Damn it.

07:19.712 --> 07:23.712
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Blue Bloods 5x01 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>Partners</font>
